{
  "id": "NXqpbY3F",
  "slug": "coxinha-utilities",
  "title": "Coxinha Utilities",
  "description": "An addon for Kibe Utilities, adding even more random and always unoriginal things.",
  "body": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&lrm;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"center\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/wEPrWd1.png\" alt=\"Coxinha Utilities's logo\" width=\"160\" height=\"160\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>Coxinha Utilities</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A standalone utility mod adding random and <del>mostly</del> always unoriginal things. Better with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/kibe\">Kibe Utilities</a><span style=\"font-size: 8px;\"><em> [1.19.4 and above]</em></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 8px;\">An addon for <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/kibe\">Kibe Utilities</a>, adding even more random and <del>mostly</del> always unoriginal things.<span style=\"font-size: 6px;\"><em>[1.19.2 and below]</em></span></span><br /><br /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Main Features</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Portable Tanks</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/iqlnzCN.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Portable Tanks</strong> are an upgrade for Kibe's regular Tanks with additional perks such as</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">additional storage per tier and maintaining their liquids after being broken.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Tiers:</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MK1 (Iron):</strong> 16 Buckets of Capacity;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MK2 (Gold):</strong> 32 Buckets of Capacity;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MK3 (Diamond):</strong> 64 Buckets of Capacity;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MK4 (Emerald):</strong> 128 Buckets of Capacity;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MK5 (Netherite):</strong> 512 Buckets of Capacity.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Wooden Hopper</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/7NpAGMO.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Wooden Hoppers</strong> are a cheaper alternative to regular hoppers, with two downsides:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">- Internal Storage of 1 slot only;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">- Cannot be blocked by a redstone signal.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Granny's Sink</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/Hn6H3up.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Granny's Sink</strong> may seem like your ordinary kitchen sink, but don't be so foolish: This sink has</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">the special properties of having an seemingly infinite source of water.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">How? Don't ask me. I don't know. <em>Nobody knows...</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Granny's Sink</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://imgur.com/SoGLtXO.png\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Fluid Trash Can</strong> and <strong>Energy Trash Can</strong> void fluids and energy, respectively.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">You can void either via the UI or cables/pipes connected to them.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>&nbsp;</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Drying Rack<br /></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://imgur.com/egiwGkE.png\" width=\"686\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Drying Racks</strong> are able to dry items into others after some time has passed using no fuel<strong> <br /></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Aquatic Torch</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/ljmbM2t.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Aquatic Torches</strong> are an alternative, more practical version of Sea Pickles. They will illuminate the</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">same as an regular torch, only underwater for the ease of your aquifer exploration.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Lava Sponge<br /></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://imgur.com/Zgzfpu3.png\" width=\"1024\" height=\"600\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Lava Sponges</strong> are the opposite of the regular sponges, draining Lava.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">To \"dry\" a Wet Lava Sponge, you must moist it with water, either in-world or in a Smithing Table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Upcoming Features</strong></span></p>\n<div>\n<p>- Dimensional Cakes;</p>\n<p>- Tinted Glass Pane;</p>\n<p>- Bucket Mode for Portable Tanks.</p>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Other Information</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Why \"Coxinha Utilities\"?</strong></span></p>\n<div>\n<p>Kibe Utilities's name comes both from the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kibbeh\">Middle Eastern savory</a> and the Brazilian slang \"kibe\" or \"kibar\" (to do a kibe), which means to plagiarize a thing, in reference of how most of its features are unoriginal. Being inspired by Kibe, Coxinha Utilities plays into the same joke by using another famous savory in Brazil, in this case being the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coxinha\">Coxinha</a>. So, in short; it's a meta joke inside another meta joke.</p>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Discord</strong></span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://discord.com/invite/G4PjhEf\"> <img src=\"https://discordapp.com/api/guilds/707435077679841350/embed.png?style=banner2&amp;v=2\" alt=\"\" width=\"320\" height=\"76\" /> </a></p>",
